# Git commit authorship

When creating or amending git commits in this repository:

- Use only the repository's configured local git user (`user.name` / `user.email` from `.git/config` or local overrides).
- Never add `Co-authored-by`, `Signed-off-by` for agents, or any Cursor/AI co-author trailers to commit messages.
- Never mention Cursor, agents, or AI tools in commit messages as authors or co-authors.
- If a commit message is amended or rewritten, strip any existing `Co-authored-by:` lines before finishing.
- Do not document co-author removal in the commit message (e.g. avoid phrases like "without Cursor co-author").
